{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"double","preciseIdentifier":"c:d"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"zoomLevel"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In addition to affecting the visual size and detail of features on the map,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the zoom level affects the size of the vector tiles that are loaded. At zoom","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"level 0, each tile covers the entire world map; at zoom level 1, it covers ¼","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of the world; at zoom level 2, ","type":"text"},{"text":"1","type":"text"},{"text":"⁄","type":"text"},{"text":"16","type":"text"},{"text":" of the world, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"so on.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Changing the value of this property updates the map view immediately. If you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"want to animate the change, use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"-setZoomLevel:animated:","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method instead.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The zoom level of the receiver."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/zoomLevel","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapview\/zoomlevel"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyP